{"word":"κυμαίνω","slug":"κυμαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κυμαίνω</b></el> <el>(κῡμαίνω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κῦμα'><el>κῦμα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to rise in waves</i> or <i>billows, to swell</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of passion, <i>to swell, seethe</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to agitate</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}